-- Sitel says shareholders vote for merger with ClientLogic
-- 
-- Fri Jan 12, 2007 5:03pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/12/us-sitel-takeover-clientlogic-idUSWNAS725020070112

 

 (Reuters) - ClientLogic Corp., a unit of Canadian conglomerate Onex Corp. ( OCX.TO ), said Sitel Corp.'s SWW.N shareholders voted to approve the proposed merger with ClientLogic. 

 More than 97 percent of voted shares were in favor of the merger. The merger is expected to close in late January or early February 2007, the companies said in a statement. The shareholders of Sitel, which provides outsourced customer support services, will receive $4.25 per share in cash. (Reporting by Rakesh Sharma in Bangalore)